<reg_short_dscr>:
Fragment configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Threshold used for invalidating L4 frames in S2.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
If set, S2 key field L3_FRAGMENT_TYPE encodes Jaguar2-style fragmentation information in CLM:
L3_FRAGMENT_TYPE[0]: Set if IPv4 frame is fragmented (MF==1 or FO>0).
L3_FRAGMENT_TYPE[1]: Set if IPv4 frame is fragmented but not the first fragment (FO>0),

If cleared, S2 key field L3_FRAGMENT_TYPE encodes the following values:
0: No Fragments: MF==0 and FO==0
1: Initial Fragments: MF==1 and FO == 0
2: Suspicious Fragment: FO!=0 and FO <= VCAP_S2_FRAGMENT_CFG.FRAGMENT_OFFSET_THRES.
3: Valid Follow-up Fragment: FO > VCAP_S2_FRAGMENT_CFG.FRAGMENT_OFFSET_THRES.

MF: More Fragments flag in IPv4 header.
FO: Fragment offset in IPv4 header.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Fragment offset threshold is used.
1: Fragment offset threshold is not used.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Threshold used for encoding of the L3_FRAGMENT_TYPE field in S2.
